From David Rind Subject Re Candida yeast Bloom Fact or Fiction In article writes oxygen just like it does in the vagina As much stuff as there is in the lay press about acidophilus and vaginal yeast infections I'm really amazed that someone has not done a clinical trial yet to check it I've mentioned this study a couple of times now Ingestion of yogurt containing Lactobacillus acidophilus as prophylaxis for candidal vaginitis Annals of Internal Medicine Do you have a problem with the study because they used yogurt rather than capsules of lactobacillus even though it had positive results The study was a crossover trial of daily ingestion of ounces of There was a marked decrease in infections while women were ingesting the Problems with the study included very small numbers patients enrolled and many protocol violations only patients were analyzed Still the difference in rates of infection between the two groups was so large that the study remains fairly David Rind